sTwTory
    &w&para <b>Exercise 3. Respond to each question or phrase in a complete sentence in modern English.</b>
    </p>
    <ol>
        <li>
            Art þou coming home anon?
            <br>&#9758\;
            I know I have been digging for hours and my shovel dull, but I cannot until I find my sanity.
        </li>
        <li>
            Should I bring aught to þe party?
            <br>&#9758\;
            May you please bring a kilogramme of ANFO for þe children to play?
        </li>
        <li>
            God-den coz!
            <br>&#9758\;
        </li>
        <li>
            Wilt þou come hiþer?
            <br>&#9758\;
            Depends\; do you have a dollar?
        </li>
        <li>
            Do you þink you can pass a class by deluding your teacher?
            <br>&#9758\;
            Pipe down, you anencephalous sub, you'll blow my cover!
        </li>
        <li>
            What preferment do you desire?
            <br>&#9758\;
            See, my last has me here, a guard to þe slums, so I wish for no more.
        </li>
        <li>
            Coz, wilt þou be home ere morning?
            <br>&#9758\;
            Probably not. My flight has been delayed a few hours.
        </li>
    </ol>
;
